{"title_page": "Shorea agamii", "text_new": "{{short description|Species of plant}}\n{{Speciesbox\n|status = EN\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|status_ref = <ref name=IUCN/>\n|genus = Shorea\n|species = agamii\n|authority = [[Peter Shaw Ashton|P.S.Ashton]]<ref name = Ashton/>\n}}\n\n'''''Shorea agamii''''' is a species of plant in the family [[Dipterocarpaceae]]. The species is named after J. Agama a one time forest officier in the Sabah Forestry Department. Two subspecies are recognised subsp. ''agamii'' and subsp ''diminuta''.<ref name = Ashton/> The subspecies name ''diminuta'' is derived from [[Latin]] (''diminutus'' = made small) and refers to the smaller leaves of this subspecies.\n\n''S. agamii'' is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Borneo]]. It is an [[Rainforest#Emergent layer|emergent]] tree, up to 50 m tall, in mixed [[dipterocarp forest]] on well-drained sandy clay soils and clay-rich soils.<ref name = Ashton/> It is a light hardwood sold under the trade names of  '''[[Dipterocarp Timber classification|white meranti]]'''. The species is incorrectly listed in the IUCN redlist as ''Shorea agami''.<ref name=IUCN/><ref name=RBC/> ''S. agamii'' subsp. ''agamii'' is found in at least three protected areas (Kabilli-[[Sepilok]] Forest Reserve, [[Lambir National Park|Lambir]] & [[Gunung Mulu National Park|Gunung Mulu]] National Parks), but is threatened elsewhere due to [[habitat loss]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist | 30em | refs =\n<ref name=IUCN>{{Cite journal | author = Ashton, P. | title = ''Shorea agami'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 1998 | page = e.T31910A9667301 | date = 1998 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/31910/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T31910A9667301.en | access-date = 23 December 2017}}</ref>\n<ref name=Ashton>{{Cite book | last1 = Ashton | first1 = P. S. |date=September 2004 | contribution = ''Shorea agamii'' P.S.Ashton | contribution-url = http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/backup/TFSS.vol4_5_6.pdf | editor1-last = Soepadmo | editor1-first = E. | editor2-last = Saw | editor2-first = L. G. | editor3-last = Chung | editor3-first = R. C. K. | title = Tree Flora of Sabah and Sarawak | volume = 5 | pages = 220\u2013221 | publisher = [[Forest Research Institute Malaysia]] | isbn = 978-983-2181-59-0 | url = http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/Resources/Publications/Books/Floras/Tree-Flora-of-Sabah-and-Sarawak.aspx | version = (free online from the publisher, lesser resolution scan PDF versions) | accessdate = 12 November 2007 }}</ref>\n<ref name=RBC>{{cite web | url = http://193.62.154.38/cgi-bin/nph-readbtree.pl/diptaxsh/maxvals=10/firstval=1?GENUS_XREF=Shorea&SPECIES_XREF=agami | title = Dipterocarpaceae Data Base Taxonomic ''Shorea agamii'' | publisher = Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh | accessdate= 12 November 2007 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5478942}}\n\n[[Category:Shorea|agamii]]\n[[Category:Endemic flora of Borneo]]\n[[Category:Trees of Borneo]]\n[[Category:Endangered plants]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Species of plant}}\n{{Speciesbox\n|status = EN\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|status_ref = <ref name=IUCN/>\n|genus = Shorea\n|species = agamii\n|authority = [[Peter Shaw Ashton|P.S.Ashton]]<ref name = Ashton/>\n}}\n\n'''''Shorea agamii''''' is a species of plant in the family [[Dipterocarpaceae]]. The species is named after J. Agama a one time forest officier in the Sabah Forestry Department. Two subspecies are recognised subsp. ''agamii'' and subsp ''diminuta''.<ref name = Ashton/> The subspecies name ''diminuta'' is derived from [[Latin]] (''diminutus'' = made small) and refers to the smaller leaves of this subspecies.\n\n''S. agamii'' is [[Endemism|endemic]] to [[Borneo]]. It is an [[Rainforest#Emergent layer|emergent]] tree, up to 50 m tall, in mixed [[dipterocarp forest]] on well-drained sandy clay soils and clay-rich soils.<ref name = Ashton/> It is a light hardwood sold under the trade names of  '''[[Dipterocarp Timber classification|White Meranti]]'''. The species is incorrectly listed in the IUCN redlist as ''Shorea agami''.<ref name=IUCN/><ref name=RBC/> ''S. agamii'' subsp. ''agamii'' is found in at least three protected areas (Kabilli-[[Sepilok]] Forest Reserve, [[Lambir National Park|Lambir]] & [[Gunung Mulu National Park|Gunung Mulu]] National Parks), but is threatened elsewhere due to [[habitat loss]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist | 30em | refs =\n<ref name=IUCN>{{Cite journal | author = Ashton, P. | title = ''Shorea agami'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 1998 | page = e.T31910A9667301 | date = 1998 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/31910/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T31910A9667301.en | access-date = 23 December 2017}}</ref>\n<ref name=Ashton>{{Cite book | last1 = Ashton | first1 = P. S. |date=September 2004 | contribution = ''Shorea agamii'' P.S.Ashton | contribution-url = http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/backup/TFSS.vol4_5_6.pdf | editor1-last = Soepadmo | editor1-first = E. | editor2-last = Saw | editor2-first = L. G. | editor3-last = Chung | editor3-first = R. C. K. | title = Tree Flora of Sabah and Sarawak | volume = 5 | pages = 220\u2013221 | publisher = [[Forest Research Institute Malaysia]] | isbn = 978-983-2181-59-0 | url = http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/Resources/Publications/Books/Floras/Tree-Flora-of-Sabah-and-Sarawak.aspx | version = (free online from the publisher, lesser resolution scan PDF versions) | accessdate = 12 November 2007 }}</ref>\n<ref name=RBC>{{cite web | url = http://193.62.154.38/cgi-bin/nph-readbtree.pl/diptaxsh/maxvals=10/firstval=1?GENUS_XREF=Shorea&SPECIES_XREF=agami | title = Dipterocarpaceae Data Base Taxonomic ''Shorea agamii'' | publisher = Royal Botanic Garden, Edinburgh | accessdate= 12 November 2007 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q5478942}}\n\n[[Category:Shorea|agamii]]\n[[Category:Endemic flora of Borneo]]\n[[Category:Trees of Borneo]]\n[[Category:Endangered plants]]\n", "name_user": "WolfmanSF", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\