Foreign Player]]: 2015\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518100656/http://www.atletico.com.br/profissional/lucas-pratto/ |title=Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro official profile}} {{in lang|pt}}\n* {{ESPN FC|109909<!-- /lucas-pratto -->}}\n* {{Soccerway|lucas-david-pratto/17657}}\n* [http://www.ogol.com.br/jogador.php?id=47630 Lucas Pratto profile] at OGol {{in lang|pt}}\n\n{{River Plate squad}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title=Awards\n|bg=gold\n|fg=black\n|list1=\n{{Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n top scorers}}\n{{Argentine Footballer of the Year}}\n{{2015 Bola de Prata}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pratto, Lucas}}\n[[Category:Sportspeople from La Plata]]\n[[Category:Argentine footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate sportspeople in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Boca Juniors footballers]]\n[[Category:Club Atl\u00e9tico Tigre footballers]]\n[[Category:Lyn Fotball players]]\n[[Category:Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe footballers]]\n[[Category:Club Deportivo Universidad Cat\u00f3lica footballers]]\n[[Category:Genoa C.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield footballers]]\n[[Category:Clube Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro players]]\n[[Category:S\u00e3o Paulo FC players]]\n[[Category:River Plate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Brazil]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Chile]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Norway]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Eliteserien players]]\n[[Category:Chilean Primera Divisi\u00f3n players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Campeonato Brasileiro S\u00e9rie A players]]\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Argentina international footballers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Lucas Pratto\n| image = Palestino - River Plate 20190424 24.jpg\n| image_size = \n|caption = Pratto with [[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]]  in 2018\n| fullname = Lucas David Pratto\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1988|6|4|df=y}} \n| birth_place = [[La Plata]], Argentina\n| height = 1.87 m\n| position = [[Forward (association football)#Striker|Striker]]\n| currentclub = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]]\n| clubnumber = 27\n| youthyears1 = 2002\u20132005\n| youthclubs1 = [[Defensores de Cambaceres|Cambaceres]]\n| youthyears2 = 2006\u20132007\n| youthclubs2 = [[Boca Juniors]]\n| years1 = 2007\u20132011\n| clubs1 = [[Boca Juniors]]\n| caps1 = 2\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Tigre|Tigre]] (loan)\n| caps2 = 13\n| goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2008\u20132009\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Lyn Fotball]] (loan)\n| caps3 = 21\n| goals3 = 4\n| years4 = 2010\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe|Uni\u00f3n]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 19\n| goals4 = 6\n| years5 = 2010\u20132011\n| clubs5 = \u2192 [[Club Deportivo Universidad Cat\u00f3lica|U. Cat\u00f3lica]] (loan)\n| caps5 = 35\n| goals5 = 10 <!--ONLY LEAGUE APPS & GOALS-->\n| years6 = 2011\u20132012\n| clubs6 = [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]]\n| caps6 = 14\n| goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2012\n| clubs7 = \u2192 [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]] (loan)\n| caps7 = 12\n| goals7 = 2\n| years8 = 2012\u20132014\n| clubs8 = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]]\n| caps8 = 85\n| goals8 = 33\n| years9 = 2015\u20132017\n| clubs9 = [[Clube Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro|Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro]]\n| caps9 = 54\n| goals9 = 18\n| years10 = 2017\n| clubs10 = [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]]\n| caps10 = 35\n| goals10 = 7\n| years11 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs11 = [[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]]\n| caps11 = 46\n| goals11 = 7\n| nationalyears1 = 2016\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 2\n| pcupdate = 5 january 2020\n| ntupdate = 28 March 2017\n}}\n\n'''Lucas David Pratto''' ({{IPA-es|\u02c8lukas da\u02c8\u03b2i\u00f0 \u02c8p\u027eato}}; born 4 June 1988) is an Argentine professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]] as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]].\n\nHe has been described as possessing unusual technique and ball control for a player of strong physique.<ref name=\"falcao\">{{Cite news|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/atletico-mg/noticia/2015/10/pratto-ganha-elogios-do-craque-falcao-e-o-durao-mais-bom-de-bola-que-ja-vi.html|title=Pratto ganha elogios do craque Falc\u00e3o: \"\u00c9 o dur\u00e3o mais bom de bola que j\u00e1 vi\"|trans-title=Pratto receives compliments of ace Falc\u00e3o: \"He's the best tough player I've ever seen\"|work = [[Grupo Globo|Globoesporte.com]]|date=15 October 2015|access-date=15 October 2015|language=pt}}</ref><ref name=\"fage\">{{Cite web|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/platb/futebolargentino/2014/12/11/conheca-o-atacante-argentino-lucas-pratto-novo-reforco-do-galo/|title=Conhe\u00e7a o atacante argentino Lucas Pratto, novo refor\u00e7o do Galo|trans-title=Meet Argentine forward Lucas Pratto, new signing of Galo|work=Futebol Argentino|publisher=[[Grupo Globo|Globoesporte.com]]|date=11 December 2014|access-date=15 October 2015|language=pt}}</ref> Pratto's first professional club was [[Boca Juniors]], by whom he was loaned to Argentine sides [[Club Atl\u00e9tico Tigre|Tigre]] and [[Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe|Uni\u00f3n]], Norway's Lyn Fotball and Chile's [[Club Deportivo Universidad Cat\u00f3lica|Universidad Cat\u00f3lica]]. He then made a permanent move to Italian club [[Genoa C.F.C.|Genoa]], before returning to his native country to play for [[Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]], first on loan and then permanently. Pratto then moved to Brazil, playing two years for [[Clube Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro|Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro]] before joining Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate. In 2014, while playing for V\u00e9lez, he was elected [[Footballer of the Year of Argentina]].<ref name=\":1\">{{cite web |url = http://www.goal.com/es-ar/news/4493/curiosidades/2014/12/17/7155582/lucas-pratto-y-%C3%A1ngel-di-mar%C3%ADa-ganaron-el-olimpia-de-plata|title = Lucas Pratto y \u00c1ngel Di Mar\u00eda ganaron el Olimpia de plata|publisher = Goal.com|accessdate = 4 May 2015|language = Spanish|date = 17 December 2014|trans-title = Lucas Pratto and \u00c1ngel Di M\u00e1ria have won the Olimpia de plata}}</ref>\n\nPratto has been capped at international level for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]].\n\n== Early life ==\nPratto was born in [[La Plata]], where he lived most of his early life in the Altos de San Lorenzo neighborhood.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://diariohoy.net/el-clasico/el-barrio-de-los-hornos-cuna-de-grandes-figuras-del-deporte-en-el-2012-5159|title = El barrio de Los Hornos, cuna de grandes figuras del deporte en el 2012|date = 31 December 2012|accessdate = 6 August 2015|website = Diario Hoy|publisher = Diario Hoy|language = Spanish|trans-title = The Los Hornos neighborhood: cradle of great sportspeople of 2012|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161011052304/http://diariohoy.net/el-clasico/el-barrio-de-los-hornos-cuna-de-grandes-figuras-del-deporte-en-el-2012-5159|archive-date = 11 October 2016|url-status = dead}}</ref> He started playing in local club Gimnasia of the Los Hornos neighborhood, and was rejected by the youth ranks of [[Estudiantes de La Plata]] before eventually making it into the [[Defensores de Cambaceres]] youth team, where his brother then played.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.elgrafico.com.ar/2013/11/11/C-4972-pratto-volvi-para-ser-feliz.php|title = Pratto: \"Volv\u00ed para ser feliz\"|date = 11 November 2013|work = [[El Gr\u00e1fico]]|access-date = 1 August 2015|language = Spanish|trans-title = Pratto: \"I came back to be happy\"}}</ref>\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Early career and loan spells===\nProduct of Defensores de Cambaceres lower divisions, Pratto joined Argentine club Boca Juniors in 2006, after a recommendation by [[Mart\u00edn Palermo]]. Once in the [[La Boca]]-based team, he was sent to the team's fifth division, where he scored more than 20 goals and formed an attacking partnership with [[\u00d3scar Trejo]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url = http://www.ellitoral.com/index.php/id_um/47904-pratto-es-el-delantero-que-pretende-union|title = Pratto es el delantero que pretende Uni\u00f3n|date = 21 December 2009|work = [[El Litoral]]|access-date = 1 August 2015|trans-title = Pratto is the forward wanted by Uni\u00f3n|language = Spanish|last = Andreychuk|first = Ignacio}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2007, he was loaned to Tigre,<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://tigrecorazon.wordpress.com/2007/08/24/lucas-pratto-nuevo-refuerzo-matador/|title = Lucas Pratto, nuevo refuerzo Matador.|date = 24 August 2007|accessdate = 1 August 2015|website = Tigre Corazon|publisher = |last = |first = |language = Spanish|trans-title = Lucas pratto, new Matador signing}}</ref> but mostly played for the [[reserve team]] in their first season. [[Leandro L\u00e1zzaro]]'s departure to Estudiantes,<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.perfil.com/deportes/Leandro-Lazzaro-abandono-Tigre-y-se-fue-a-Estudiantes-20080116-0037.html|title = Leandro L\u00e1zzaro abandon\u00f3 Tigre y se fue a Estudiantes|last = |first = |date = 16 January 2008|work = [[Perfil]]|access-date = 13 July 2014|via = |language = Spanish|trans-title = Leandro L\u00e1zzaro left Tigre and joined Estudiantes}}</ref> however, allowed Pratto to break into the starting eleven and challenge the possibility of being the team's first choice striker. Following L\u00e1zzaro's absence, Lucas played ten [[2007-08 in Argentine football|2008 Clausura]] games and scored one goal against [[San Mart\u00edn de San Juan]], which was his side's winning goal in a 2\u20131 home win at [[Estadio Jos\u00e9 Dellagiovanna|Jos\u00e9 Dellagiovanna]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://edant.clarin.com/diario/2008/05/23/um/m-01678368.htm|title = Tigre le dio otro empuj\u00f3n a San Mart\u00edn|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = Clarin.com|language = Spanish|date = 23 May 2008|trans-title = Tigre gave San Mart\u00edn another bump}}</ref>\n\nOn 2 August 2008, Pratto joined Norway's Lyn Fotball on a free loan from Boca, after being recommended by the scout [[Terje Liver\u00f8d]] who helped with the negotiations.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.ole.clarin.com/notas/2008/08/02/futbollocal/01728664.html|title = Mercado de pases|date = 2 August 2008|work = [[Ol\u00e9 (sports newspaper)|Ol\u00e9]]|access-date = 1 August 2015|language = Spanish|trans-title = Transfer market|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20080805052853/http://www.ole.clarin.com/notas/2008/08/02/futbollocal/01728664.html|archive-date = 5 August 2008|url-status = dead}}</ref> On 15 August, Lucas made a goalscoring debut during a 3\u20131 defeat against [[Molde FK]] in a [[Tippeligaen]] game as a 71st-minute substitute. Between 2008 and 2009 Pratto made 21 league appearances and scored four goals for Lyn.<ref name=\"Pratto \u2013 Football Lineups\">{{cite web|url = http://www.football-lineups.com/footballer/13579/?t=183&s=1012|title = Lucas Pratto Tippeligaen 2008|accessdate = 13 July 2014|website = Football-Lineups}}</ref> He then returned to Argentina in mid-2009 to join Boca's first-team squad, then coached by [[Alfio Basile]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nAfter once again not being considered at the [[La Bombonera]] squad, Pratto had another brief loan spell in the first half of 2010, this time at Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe in the [[Primera B Nacional]].\n\n=== Universidad Cat\u00f3lica ===\nOn 29 June 2010 Pratto joined Chile's Universidad Cat\u00f3lica on loan from Boca, this time as part of [[Gary Medel]]'s contract extension negotiation.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.emol.com/noticias/deportes/2010/06/29/421681/lucas-pratto-es-el-nuevo-delantero-de-universidad-catolica.html|title = Lucas Pratto es el nuevo delantero de Universidad Cat\u00f3lica|date = 29 June 2010|work = [[El Mercurio]]|access-date = 1 August 2015|trans-title = Lucas Pratto is Universidad Cat\u00f3lica's new forward|language = Spanish}}</ref> In the Chilean club, Pratto scored in his debut against [[Everton de Vi\u00f1a del Mar|Everton]] in a 1\u20131 league draw at [[Vi\u00f1a del Mar]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.cducatolica.com/cducatolica/24/07/2010/everton-1-1-u-catolica-1%C2%BA-rueda-2010/|title = Everton 1 \u2013 1 U. Cat\u00f3lica (1\u00ba rueda 2010)|date = 24 July 2010|publisher = Cducatolica.com|language = Spanish|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110706120445/http://www.cducatolica.com/cducatolica/24/07/2010/everton-1-1-u-catolica-1%C2%BA-rueda-2010/|archivedate = 6 July 2011|df = dmy-all}}</ref> At first, Lucas was heavily criticized for his bad shape at the [[Las Condes]]-based team, but key goals in the end of the season against [[Club Universidad de Chile|Universidad de Chile]]<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.mercuriovalpo.cl/prontus4_noticias/site/artic/20101121/pags/20101121190822.html|title = Universidad Cat\u00f3lica vence por 4-2 a U. de Chile|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = El Mercurio de Valpara\u00edso|language = Spanish|trans-title = Universidad Catolica defeats U. De Chile by 4-2|date = 21 November 2010}}</ref> and [[Cobreloa]]<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.mercurioantofagasta.cl/prontus4_noticias/site/artic/20101127/pags/20101127180758.html|title = Cat\u00f3lica hace el milagro: 3-2 le gana a Cobreloa|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = El Mercurio de Antofagasta|language = Spanish|date = 27 November 2010|trans-title = Cat\u00f3lica makes a miracle: defeats Cobreloa 3-2}}</ref> helped Cat\u00f3lica achieve their 10th [[Chilean Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Campeonato Nacional]] title.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.biobiochile.cl/2010/12/05/lucas-pratto-la-gente-no-se-merecia-salir-segundo.shtml|title = Lucas Pratto: \u2018La gente no se merec\u00eda salir segundo\u2019|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = BioBioChile|language = Spanish|trans-title = Lucas Pratto: 'We did not deserve to be runners-up'|date = 5 December 2010|last = Gonzalez|first = Alberto|website = BioBioChile}}</ref> He had an impressive season start in 2011 when he scored six [[2011 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores]] goals (including a brace against [[Gr\u00eamio Foot-Ball Porto Alegrense|Gr\u00eamio]], in a historic 2\u20131 triumph at [[Brazil]])<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.emol.com/noticias/deportes/2011/04/26/478227/pratto-enmudece-porto-alegre-tras-gran-victoria-de-la-uc-sobre-gremio-por-la-libertadores.html|title = Pratto enmudece a Porto Alegre tras gran victoria de la UC sobre Gremio en la Libertadores|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = [[El Mercurio]]|language = Spanish|date = 26 April 2011|trans-title = Pratto silences Porto Alegre after great UC victory over Gremio in Libertadores}}</ref> and six league goals, which allowed him be sold by Boca to [[Serie A|Italian Serie A]] side Genoa for a [[US$]]2,4 million fee.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://diario.latercera.com/2011/04/29/01/contenido/deportes/4-67399-9-la-opcion-de-compra-de-lucas-pratto-es-barata.shtml|title = La opci\u00f3n de compra de Lucas Pratto es barata|date = 29 April 2011|publisher = [[La Tercera]]|language = Spanish|accessdate = 1 August 2015|trans-title = Lucas Pratto's signing option is cheap|last = Casta\u00f1aga|first = Enrique}}</ref>\n\n===Genoa===\nPratto joined the Genovese club on 30 June 2011,<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.planetafichajes.net/2011/06/pratto-nuevo-delantero-para-el-genoa.html|title = Pratto, el nuevo delantero para el Genoa|date = 30 June 2011|publisher = Planetafichajes.net|language = Spanish|trans-title = Pratto, the new forward for Genoa}}</ref> being described months before by the club's president [[Enrico Preziosi]] as the team's new [[Diego Milito]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.latercera.com/noticia/deportes/2011/05/656-368328-9-en-genoa-esperan-a-lucas-pratto-como-el-nuevo-diego-milito.shtml|title = En Genoa esperan a Lucas Pratto como \"el nuevo Diego Milito\"|date = 25 May 2011|publisher = [[La Tercera]]|language = Spanish|trans-title = At Genoa Lucas Pratto is expected as \"the new Diego Milito\"|accessdate = 1 August 2015}}</ref> He officially debuted as a starter during Genoa's first [[2011\u201312 Coppa Italia]] game against [[A.S.G. Nocerina|Nocerina]] in a 4\u20133 home win,<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.larazon.com.ar/deportes/Lucas-Pratto-comenzo-hacer-Genoa_0_266700049.html|title = Lucas Pratto comenz\u00f3 a hacer goles en el Genoa|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = [[La Raz\u00f3n (Buenos Aires)|La Raz\u00f3n]]|language = Spanish|date = 10 August 2011|trans-title = Lucas Pratto started scoring goals at Genoa|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160826144039/http://www.larazon.com.ar/deportes/Lucas-Pratto-comenzo-hacer-Genoa_0_266700049.html|archive-date = 26 August 2016|url-status = dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.elcomercio.es/agencias/20110820/deportes/futbol/rodrigo-palacio-lucas-pratto-mantienen_201108202157.html|title = Rodrigo Palacio y Lucas Pratto mantienen al G\u00e9nova en la Copa|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = [[El Comercio (Spain)|El Comercio]]|language = Spanish|date = 20 August 2011|trans-title = Rodrigo Palacio and Lucas Pratto keep Genoa in the Cup}}</ref> in which he scored his side's second goal after an assist by [[K\u00e9vin Constant]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.football-lineups.com/match/112216/|title = Genoa vs Nocerina Coppa Italia 2011/2012|accessdate = 13 July 2014|website = Football-Lineups}}</ref> His Serie A debut was on 11 September in a 2\u20132 draw with [[Atalanta B.C.|Atalanta]] for the league's first matchday, and his first goal came on 18 December in a 2\u20131 victory over [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]], the match-winner at the 85th minute.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://redgol.cl/2011/12/jorquera-ingreso-en-gran-triunfo-del-genoa/|title = Jorquera ingres\u00f3 en gran triunfo del Genoa|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = Red Gol|language = Spanish|date = 18 December 2011|trans-title = Jorquera came in<!--not a mistake--> in Genoa's great triumph|last = Arellano|first = Francisco|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180819052654/https://redgol.cl/2011/12/jorquera-ingreso-en-gran-triunfo-del-genoa/|archive-date = 19 August 2018|url-status = dead}}</ref> His second goal for Coppa Italia was on 24 November against [[AS Bari|Bari]] in a 3\u20132 victory, where once again he scored the match's winning goal, now after an impressive header in the 115th minute during [[extra-time]].<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.seleccionchilena.cl/copa-italia-jorquera-marco-en-la-victoria-del-genoa-frente-al-bari-por-3-2-video/|title = Jorquera marc\u00f3 en la victoria del Genoa frente al Bari|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = Selecci\u00f3n Chilena|language = Spanish|date = 25 November 2011|trans-title = Jorquera scored in Genoa's victory against Bari}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://diario.latercera.com/2011/11/25/01/contenido/deportes/4-91733-9-jorquera-y-pratto-anotan-para-genoa.shtml|title = Jorquera y Pratto anotan para Genoa|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = [[La Tercera]]|language = Spanish|date = 25 November 2011|trans-title = Jorquera and Pratto score for Genoa}}</ref> Pratto made an attacking partnership with [[Rodrigo Palacio]], but coach [[Alberto Malesani]], by whom he was selected for the first squad, was fired in December 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.biobiochile.cl/2012/04/23/alberto-malesani-fue-destituido-como-entrenador-del-genoa-de-cristobal-jorquera.shtml|title = Alberto Malesani fue destituido como entrenador del Genoa de Crist\u00f3bal Jorquera|accessdate = 13 July 2014|publisher = Bio Bi\u00f3 Chile|language = Spanish|date = 23 April 2012|trans-title = Alberto Malesani sacked as Crist\u00f3bal Jorquera's Genoa manager|first = Sim\u00f3n|last = Collado}}</ref> Since that time Lucas failed to play the rest of season, being relegated to the bench by the team's next coaches ([[Pasquale Marino]], the same Malesani and [[Luigi De Canio]]).<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.football-lineups.com/footballer/13579/?t=749&s=311|title = Lucas Pratto Serie A 2011/12|accessdate = 13 July 2014|website = Football-Lineups}}</ref>\n\n===V\u00e9lez Sarsfield===\n{{quote box|width=33%|align=right|quote=\"Pratto's football matches mine. We understood each other pretty quickly. I don't have his strength, nor his guts. I don't know where he takes it from. I did not expect for him to be so technical. When I saw him training, I realized I had a great passer by my side.\"|source=\u2014[[Facundo Ferreyra]], Pratto's attack partner in V\u00e9lez Sarsfield, about his style of play.<ref name=\"fage\"/>}}\n[[File:Pratto Velez Penarol 2013.jpg|thumb|Pratto playing for V\u00e9lez in the [[2013 Copa Libertadores]].]]\nOn 7 February 2012 it was reported that Pratto had joined [[CA V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|V\u00e9lez Sarsfield]] in a season-long loan deal, with the option to be fully signed by the Argentine club.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://calcio.attualissimo.it/ufficiale-pratto-dal-genoa-al-velez/|title = Ufficiale, Pratto dal Genoa al Velez|last = Vanacore|first = Ernesto|date = 7 February 2012|work = Attualissimo.it Clacio|access-date = 6 August 2015|via = }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.velezsarsfield.com.ar/futbol/notas/2012/02/10/152743.html|title = Cuando me llamaron dije que s\u00ed sin dudarlo|author = Carlos Alberto Martino|publisher = Club Atl\u00e9tico V\u00e9lez Sarsfield|language = Spanish|date = 10 February 2012|accessdate = 27 February 2012|trans-title = When they called me I said yes without a doubt}}</ref> After a decent first season with the [[Liniers]] side, in which he played 20 times and scored 4 goals, Lucas became a starter during V\u00e9lez's [[2012\u201313 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n season#Torneo Inicial|2012 Torneo Inicial]] championship-winning campaign. Pratto made a partnership with [[Facundo Ferreyra]], and played a key role appearing in all 19 games and scoring seven goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.argentinesoccer.com/player_apps.cfm?id=prto&Championship=in12&Team=vel |title=Inicial '12 statistics |publisher=Argentine Soccer |accessdate=24 December 2012 }}</ref>\n\nIn January 2013 it was reported that V\u00e9lez had come to an agreement with Genoa for the definitive purchase of the player on a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://deportes.terra.com.ar/futbol/velez-retiene-a-uno-de-sus-goleadores-lucas-pratto,14fb550d5112c310VgnCLD2000000dc6eb0aRCRD.html|title = V\u00e9lez retiene a uno de sus goleadores, Lucas Pratto|date = 10 January 2013|work = [[Terra Networks|Terra]]|access-date = 31 July 2015|language = Spanish|trans-title = V\u00e9lez keeps one of its goalscorers, Lucas Pratto}}</ref> On 29 June 2013, Lucas scored the match winner in the Superfinal, the match that concluded the [[2012\u201313 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n season|2012\u201313 Primera Divisi\u00f3n season]], as V\u00e9lez defeated [[Newell's Old Boys|Newell's]] 1\u20130 and were crowned Super Champions. At the end of the year Pratto was selected as V\u00e9lez's best player of the season.\n\nIn the start of 2014 he won the [[2013 Supercopa Argentina|Supercopa Argentina]] with his club, and was the top goalscorer of the [[2014 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n|Torneo de Transici\u00f3n]], with 11 goals. For his performances Pratto was once again selected as V\u00e9lez's player of the year, and was honored with the [[Olimpia de Plata]] award as Footballer of the Year of Argentina, chosen by Argentine sports media as the best player in the local league.<ref name=\":1\" />\n\n===Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro===\nOn 16 December 2014, Lucas Pratto joined Brazilian club Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|title = Lucas Pratto refor\u00e7a o Galo|url = http://www.atletico.com.br/lucas-pratto-reforca-o-galo/|website = Clube Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro|accessdate = 17 December 2014|language = Portuguese|date = 16 December 2014|trans-title = Lucas Pratto joins Galo}}</ref> Pratto made his unofficial debut and scored his first goal for Atl\u00e9tico in a pre-season friendly against [[Shakhtar Donetsk]], which his new team won 4\u20132.<ref>{{cite web|title = Atl\u00e9tico-MG vence Shakhtar sem dificuldade com gol do estreante Pratto|url = http://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2015/01/21/atletico-mg-vence-shakhtar-sem-dificuldade-com-gol-do-estreante-pratto.htm|website = [[Universo Online|UOL Esporte]]|accessdate = 4 May 2015|language = Portuguese|date = 21 January 2015|trans-title = Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro defeats Shakhtar without difficulties with a goal by newcomer Pratto}}</ref> Pratto also scored in his first official match for the club, against [[Tupi Football Club|Tupi]], for the 2015 [[Campeonato Mineiro]],<ref>{{cite web |url = http://espn.uol.com.br/noticia/480724_com-gols-de-datolo-e-pratto-atletico-mg-abre-2015-com-vitoria-sobre-o-tupi|title = Com gols de D\u00e1tolo e Pratto, Atl\u00e9tico-MG abre 2015 com vit\u00f3ria sobre o Tupi|publisher = [[ESPN Brasil]]|accessdate = 4 May 2015|language = Portuguese|date = 1 February 2015|trans-title = With goals by D\u00e1tolo and Pratto, Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro starts 2015 with victory against Tupi}}</ref> as well as in his debut in [[2015 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores]] for Atl\u00e9tico, scoring the winner in a 1\u20130 away win against [[Independiente Santa F\u00e9]].<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.espn.com.ar/futbol/cronica?id=411889|title = Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro revive en el grupo 1 y allana liderato para Colo Colo|publisher = ESPN Argentina|accessdate = 4 May 2015|language = Spanish|trans-title = Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro born again in group 1 and levels Colo Colo's leadership}}</ref>\n\nIn the second leg of the [[2015 Campeonato Mineiro|Campeonato Mineiro]] semifinals against fierce rivals [[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]], Pratto managed to score a brace with two assists by [[Guilherme Milhomem Gusm\u00e3o|Guilherme]], one of the goals an impressive volley, and helped his team make a 2\u20131 comeback after trailing in half-time.<ref>{{cite web |url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/mg/futebol/campeonato-mineiro/noticia/2015/04/pratto-e-guilherme-detonam-cruzeiro-e-atletico-mg-esta-na-final-do-mineiro.html|title = Pratto e Guilherme detonam Cruzeiro, e Atl\u00e9tico-MG est\u00e1 na final do Mineiro|publisher = [[Grupo Globo|GloboEsporte.com]]|accessdate = 4 May 2015|language = Portuguese|date = 19 April 2015|trans-title = Pratto and Guilherme smash Cruzeiro, and Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro is in the Mineiro finals}}</ref> Atl\u00e9tico were eventually crowned champions of the competition, with Pratto finishing with six goals and being selected for the team of the tournament and as its best player.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite news|url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/mg/noticia/2015/05/trofeu-globo-minas-atletico-mg-tem-quatro-representantes-na-selecao-do-campeonato-mineiro.html|title = Trof\u00e9u Globo Minas: Galo tem quatro representantes na sele\u00e7\u00e3o do Mineiro|date = 3 May 2015|work = [[Grupo Globo|Globoesporte.com]]|access-date = 6 August 2015|language = Portuguese|trans-title = Trof\u00e9u Globo Minas: Galo has 4 representatives in Mineiro's best squad}}</ref><ref name=\":3\">{{cite web |url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/mg/noticia/2015/05/trofeu-globo-minas-argentino-pratto-e-eleito-craque-do-campeonato-mineiro.html|title = Trof\u00e9u Globo Minas: Lucas Pratto \u00e9 eleito craque do Campeonato Mineiro|publisher = [[Grupo Globo|GloboEsporte.com]]|accessdate = 4 May 2015|language = Portuguese|date = 3 May 2015|trans-title = Trof\u00e9u Globo Minas: Lucas Pratto elected Campeonato Mineiro best player}}</ref> In July 2015, Pratto became Atl\u00e9tico's highest-ever foreign goalscorer and scored his first-ever hat-trick, with all three goals coming in the first half of a 3\u20131 home win against [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]].<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/atletico-mg/noticia/2015/07/com-hat-trick-no-mineirao-pratto-se-isola-como-gringo-artilheiro-no-galo.html|title = In\u00e9dito hat-trick na carreira isola Pratto como artilheiro estrangeiro no Galo|date = 30 July 2015|work = [[Grupo Globo|GloboEsporte.com]]|access-date = 31 July 2015|language = Portuguese|trans-title = First career hat-trick makes Pratto Galo's sole foreign top goalscorer}}</ref>\n\n=== S\u00e3o Paulo ===\n[[File:Lucas Pratto atuando pelo S\u00e3o Paulo em 2017 (35696694401) (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|120px|Pratto with [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|S\u00e3o Paulo]] in 2017]]\nOn 10 February 2017, Pratto signed a four-year contract with Brazilian club [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC]]. The transfer totalled around \u20ac12 million, with the [[S\u00e3o Paulo]]-based club paying approximately \u20ac6 million for 50 per cent of the player's rights. According to Carlos Augusto de Barros e Silva, S\u00e3o Paulo's president, the club would acquire up to 95% of the rights in the future. Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro president Daniel Nepomuceno stated that payment for the remaining shares would occur within three years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hojeemdia.com.br/esportes/atl%C3%A9tico-vende-50-de-pratto-e-s%C3%A3o-paulo-ter%C3%A1-obriga%C3%A7%C3%A3o-de-comprar-porcentagem-restante-1.445227|title=Atl\u00e9tico vende 50% de Pratto e S\u00e3o Paulo ter\u00e1 obriga\u00e7\u00e3o de comprar porcentagem restante|trans-title=Atl\u00e9tico sells 50% of Pratto and S\u00e3o Paulo will have an obligation to buy remaining percentage|work=Hoje em Dia|language=pt|last=Ribeiro|first=Frederico|date=10 February 2017|access-date=10 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://hojeemdia.com.br/esportes/atl%C3%A9tico-vende-50-de-pratto-e-s%C3%A3o-paulo-ter%C3%A1-obriga%C3%A7%C3%A3o-de-comprar-porcentagem-restante-1.445227|title=Leco revela que S\u00e3o Paulo pode ter at\u00e9 95% dos direitos de Pratto at\u00e9 2021|trans-title=Leco reveals S\u00e3o Paulo may have up to 95% of Pratto's rights until 2021|work=[[Fox Sports (Brazil)|Fox Sports]]|language=pt|date=12 February 2017|access-date=14 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blogdoperrone.blogosfera.uol.com.br/2017/02/galo-ve-spfc-obrigado-a-comprar-mais-50-de-pratto-e-poe-valor-para-revenda/|title=Galo v\u00ea SPFC obrigado a comprar mais 50% de Pratto e p\u00f5e valor para revenda|trans-title=Galo sees SPFC obliged to buy more 50% of Pratto and stipulates resell value|work=Blog do Perrone|publisher=UOL Esporte|language=pt|last=Perrone|first=Ricardo|date=11 February 2017|access-date=14 February 2017}}</ref>\n\nHe netted in his debut for [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC|Tricolor]], in a 2\u20132 draw against [[Mirassol Futebol Clube|Mirassol]],<ref>[https://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/campeonatos/paulista/ultimas-noticias/2017/02/18/sao-paulo-x-mirassol.htm Estreia frustrada! Pratto marca, mas v\u00ea S\u00e3o Paulo ceder empate ao Mirassol]</ref> and, three days later, he scored twice in his second match for club, in a 3\u20132 victory against [[Esporte Clube S\u00e3o Bento|S\u00e3o Bento]].<ref>[https://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/campeonatos/paulista/ultimas-noticias/2017/02/21/sao-paulo-x-sao-bento.htm Pratto faz dois, p\u00eanalti compensa falhas e S\u00e3o Paulo vence S\u00e3o Bento]</ref> Pratto, along with his compatriot [[Jonathan Calleri|Calleri]], is the only debut player at the club to score in his two first official matches.<ref>[http://www.saopaulofc.net/noticias/noticias/historia/2017/2/22/pratto-e-calleri-os-unicos-estreantes-a-marcar-gols-em-dois-jogos-de-competicao-seguidos/ Pratto e Calleri: os \u00fanicos estreantes a marcar gols em dois jogos de competi\u00e7\u00e3o seguidos]</ref>\n\nOn 9 July 2017, Pratto lost a penalty kick in a 3\u20132 loss of [[S\u00e3o Paulo FC]] against rivals [[Santos FC]]. At the end of this match, he was seven consecutive games without scoring any goal.<ref>[http://jovempan.uol.com.br/esportes/futebol/sem-gols-sem-vitoria-jejum-de-pratto-e-reflexo-de-ma-fase-do-sao-paulo.html Sem gols, sem vit\u00f3ria: jejum de Pratto \u00e9 reflexo de m\u00e1 fase do S\u00e3o Paulo]</ref>\n\n===River Plate===\nOn 8 January 2018, S\u00e3o Paulo confirmed the selling of Pratto to [[Club Atl\u00e9tico River Plate|River Plate]] for \u20ac11.5 million<ref>[https://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/sao-paulo/noticia/sao-paulo-aceita-proposta-do-river-plate-por-lucas-pratto.ghtml S\u00e3o Paulo aceita proposta do River Plate e vende Lucas Pratto (in Portuguese) \"S\u00e3o Paulo accepts River's proposal and sells Lucas Pratto\"]</ref>, becoming River's highest ever transfer acquisition.<ref>[https://www.cronista.com/deportes/Pratto-ya-es-la-compra-mas-cara-de-la-historia-de-River-y-la-tercera-del-futbol-local-20180109-0023.html Pratto ya es la compra m\u00e1s cara de la historia de River y la tercera del f\u00fatbol local (in Spanish). \"Pratto already is River's most expensive buy ever and the third highest at the domestic level]\"</ref>\n\nLucas Pratto scored two goals in the historic [[2018 Copa Libertadores Finals]] against rivals [[Boca Juniors]], scoring one at each leg, thus helping River win the title.<ref>[https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/copa-libertadores/20181210/453487275444/lucas-pratto-de-promesa-de-boca-a-heroe-de-river.html Lucas Pratto: de promesa de Boca a h\u00e9roe de River (in Spanish). \"Lucas Pratto: from Boca promise to River hero\"]</ref>\n\n== International career ==\nPratto received his first international call-up for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] on 12 August 2016, for [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]] and [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://afa.com.ar/5103/la-lista-para-las-eliminatorias|title=La lista para las Eliminatorias|trans-title=The list for the qualification|date=12 August 2016|website=[[Argentine Football Association]]|access-date=14 August 2016|language=es}}</ref> He started for the national team for the first time in the match against Uruguay on 1 September 2016,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/matches/round=276453/match=300359714/index.html|title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia\u2122 - Matches - Argentina-Uruguay|date=1 September 2016|website=[[FIFA]]|access-date=1 September 2016}}</ref> and scored his first goal against Venezuela on 7 September.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/international-football/2016/09/07/57cfe791468aeb32298b46a1.html|title=Otamendi equaliser saves Argentina from Venezuela defeat|website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|date=7 September 2016|access-date=22 September 2016}}</ref> Pratto scored his second international goal helping Argentina to a 3\u20130 win over [[Colombia national football team|Colombia]] in November 2016.\n\nIn the [[Jorge Sampaoli]]'s first calling up for [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]], Pratto was not called, in spite of being remembered in [[Edgardo Bauza]]'s lists.<ref>[http://www.atribuna.com.br/noticias/noticias-detalhe/futebol/sampaoli-faz-sua-primeira-convocacao-na-argentina-para-encarar-o-brasil/?cHash=eabd93f2ed18a40ba4bf0327e0b50411 Sampaoli faz sua primeira convoca\u00e7\u00e3o na Argentina para encarar o Brasil]</ref><ref>[http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/sao-paulo/noticia/pratto-fica-fora-de-convocacao-da-argentina-e-reforca-o-sao-paulo.ghtml Pratto fica fora de convoca\u00e7\u00e3o da Argentina e \"refor\u00e7a\" o S\u00e3o Paulo]</ref>\n\n== Style of play ==\n{{quote box|width=25%|align=right|quote=\"Lucas Pratto is the best \"tough\" player I've ever seen! It seems he will lose every ball, but he hardly does.\"|source=\u2014Four-time [[Futsal Awards|Best Futsal Player in the World]] [[Falc\u00e3o (futsal player)|Falc\u00e3o]] comments on Pratto's style of play.<ref name=\"falcao\">{{Cite news|url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/atletico-mg/noticia/2015/10/pratto-ganha-elogios-do-craque-falcao-e-o-durao-mais-bom-de-bola-que-ja-vi.html|title=Pratto ganha elogios do craque Falc\u00e3o: \"\u00c9 o dur\u00e3o mais bom de bola que j\u00e1 vi\"|trans-title=Pratto receives compliments of ace Falc\u00e3o: \"He's the best tough player I've ever seen\"|work = [[Grupo Globo|Globoesporte.com]]|date=15 October 2015|access-date=15 October 2015|language=pt}}</ref>}}\nPratto has an unusually fast pace for a player with 1.88m, and frequently floats outside the box to assist other players. He has been praised for his technique, ball control, and link-up play.<ref name=\"fage\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/3297/argentina/2016/09/06/27228852/meet-lucas-pratto-the-journeyman-striker-who-has-muscled-higuain-|title=Meet Lucas Pratto: The journeyman striker who has muscled Higuain out of the Argentina team|publisher=Goal.com|author1=Daniel Edwards|date=6 September 2016|accessdate=29 March 2017}}</ref> Tactically, Pratto has not usually been deployed as a [[Forward (association football)#Centre-forward|target man centre forward]] throughout most of his career, as is commonly the case for a player with a strong physique; he has normally played as a [[Forward (association football)#Striker|striker]] or [[Forward (association football)#Second striker|second striker]]. In his best season with V\u00e9lez, he played as a second striker or even as an [[Forward (association football)#Winger|outside forward]], with Facundo Ferreyra occupying the centre-forward role.<ref name=\"fage\"/> Upon his arrival at Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro, he started to play in a more central role in the attack,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2015/01/19/lucas-pratto-admite-dificuldade-para-jogar-como-centroavante-no-atletico-mg.htm|title=Lucas Pratto admite dificuldade para jogar como centroavante no Atl\u00e9tico-MG|trans-title=Lucas Prattos admits difficulty to play as a centre-forward in Atl\u00e9tico-MG|last=Martins|first=Victor|date=19 January 2015|access-date=15 October 2015|work=[[Universo Online|UOL Esporte]]|language=pt}}</ref> while still contributing with assists and playing in the flanks during the matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://torcedores.com/noticias/2015/10/opiniao-pratto-pode-nao-estar-tao-goleador-no-atletico-mg-mas-sua-funcao-tatica-e-exemplar|title = Pratto pode n\u00e3o estar t\u00e3o goleador no Atl\u00e9tico-MG, mas sua fun\u00e7\u00e3o t\u00e1tica \u00e9 exemplar|date=6 October 2015|access-date=15 October 2015|last=Donizete|first=M\u00e1rcio|work = Torcedores.com|language=pt}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nPratto was raised by his mother Daniela, helped by his older brother Leandro. Aside from him, Lucas has three other siblings from his father's other family.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://canchallena.lanacion.com.ar/1741449-de-repartidor-de-volantes-y-patovica-a-estrella-de-futbol-la-sacrificada-vida-de-lucas-pratto|title = De no tener para comer a estrella de f\u00fatbol: la sacrificada vida de Lucas Pratto|date = 5 November 2014|accessdate = 3 August 2015|website = Cancha Llena|publisher = [[La Naci\u00f3n]]|last = Ruya|first = Ariel|trans-title = From having nothing to eat to football star: the sacrificed life of Lucas Pratto}}</ref> Pratto has one daughter, Pia, born in 2010,<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.lun.com/lunmobile//Pages/NewsDetailMobile.aspx?dt=2011-05-11&PaginaId=18&SupplementId=0&bodyid=0|title = Los mil apodos del crack que hace so\u00f1ar a la UC|last = Cordero|first = Pamela|date = 11 May 2011|work = [[Las \u00daltimas Noticias]]|access-date = 3 August 2015|trans-title = The one thousand nicknames of the ace that makes UC dream}}</ref> and has tattoos portraying her and his mother. Lucas has an interest on rock and roll, being a fan of [[AC/DC]], [[Foo Fighters]], [[Kiss (band)|Kiss]] and Argentine band [[La Renga]], of whom he also has a tattoo.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.otempo.com.br/superfc/atletico/anti-her%C3%B3i-em-preto-e-branco-1.1078189|title = Anti-her\u00f3i em preto e branco|last = Prata|first = Thiago|date = 31 July 2015|work = O Tempo|access-date = 3 August 2015|via = |trans-title = An anti-hero in black and white}}</ref> He is also an avid fan of [[The Simpsons]], has tattoos of both Homer and Bart, and an English bulldog named Santa's Little Helper.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/atletico-mg/noticia/2015/03/fa-de-simpsons-pratto-demonstra-paixao-com-tatuagens-e-homenagens.html|title = F\u00e3 de Simpsons, Pratto demonstra paix\u00e3o com tatuagens e homenagens|last = Simonini|first = L\u00e9o|date = 25 March 2015|work = [[Grupo Globo|Globoesporte.com]]|access-date = 3 August 2015|trans-title = The Simpsons fan, Pratto shows his passion with tattoos and homages}}</ref> Pratto has stated that he is a Boca Juniors supporter.<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.goal.com/br/news/11072/exclusivo/2015/03/04/9507682/lucas-pratto-admite-que-%C3%A9-torcedor-do-boca-e-fala-do-estilo|title = Lucas Pratto admite que \u00e9 torcedor do Boca e fala do estilo do t\u00e9cnico Levir Culpi: \"Gosta que a equipe esteja sempre unida\"|last = Gabin|first = Daniel|date = 4 March 2015|work = Goal.com|access-date = 3 August 2015|trans-title = Lucas Pratto admits he is a Boca fan and talks about manager Levir Culpi's style: \"He likes the team to be always together\"}}</ref> He holds an Italian passport.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.gianlucadimarzio.com/calciomercato/genoa-ecco-el-camello-pratto/|title = Genoa, ecco \"el camello\" Pratto|date = 19 May 2011|accessdate = 17 August 2015|publisher = Gianlucadimarzio.com|last = Di Marzio|first = Gianluca|trans-title = Genoa, here is \"el camello\" Pratto|language = it}}</ref>\n\n== Career statistics ==\n''Statistics accurate as of 13 October 2019.''<ref>{{Cite web|url = https://int.soccerway.com/players/lucas-david-pratto/17657/|title = Argentina - L. Pratto - Profile with news, career statistics and history - Soccerway|accessdate = 11 August 2015|website = Soccerway|publisher = Soccerway}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.ceroacero.es/player_seasons.php?id=47630|title = Lucas Pratto :: Lucas David Pratto :: Atl\u00e9tico Mineiro|accessdate = 4 August 2015|website = ceroacero.es|language = Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://espndeportes.espn.go.com/futbol/jugador/_/id/109909/lucas-pratto|title = Lucas Pratto Biograf\u00eda, Numeritos, Noticias - Futbol - - ESPN Deportes|accessdate = 4 August 2015|website = [[ESPN Deportes.com]]|language = Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.fotballen.eu/nm/maalNM09.html|title = toppscorer - NM - 2009|accessdate = 11 August 2015|website = fotballen.eu|publisher = fotballen.eu|language = no}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Club\n! rowspan=\"2\" |Season\n! colspan=\"2\" |League\n! colspan=\"2\" |Cup\n! colspan=\"2\" |Continental\n! colspan=\"2\" |State League\n! colspan=\"2\" |Total\n|-\n!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Club Atl\u00e9tico Tigre|'''Tigre''']]\n|[[2007\u201308 Argentine Primera Divisi\u00f3n season|2007\u201308]]\n|13||1|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2013|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2013|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2013||13||1\n|-\n!Total\n!13!!1!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!13!!1\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |'''[[Lyn Fotball|Lyn]]'''\n|[[2008 Tippeligaen|2008]]\n|6||1|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2013|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2013|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2013||6||1\n|-\n|[[2009 Tippeligaen|2009]]\n|15||3||4||3|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2013|| colspan=\"2\" |\u2013||19||6\n|-\n!Total\n!21!!4!!4!!3!!0!!0!!0!!0!!25!!7\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" |'''[[Boca Juniors]]'''\n|[[2009\u201310 